## A. VOCABULARY SELF-STUDY

### A1. Flashcard List (Quizlet-Ready Format)

Copy and paste this list into Quizlet or your preferred flashcard app.

```
Term | Definition | Example Sentence
-----|------------|------------------
phishing | Fraudulent attempt to obtain sensitive information by disguising as a trustworthy source | The IT team warned us about phishing emails pretending to be from our bank.
malware | Malicious software designed to damage or gain unauthorized access to systems | Our antivirus detected malware trying to install on the computer.
ransomware | Malware that encrypts data and demands payment for the decryption key | The hospital had to pay $500,000 after a ransomware attack locked all patient records.
DDoS attack | Distributed Denial of Service ‚Äî overwhelming systems with traffic to make them unavailable | The website was down for hours due to a massive DDoS attack.
social engineering | Manipulating people to reveal confidential information or take harmful actions | The attacker used social engineering to convince the receptionist to give access.
data breach | Unauthorized access to confidential data | The data breach exposed 12 million customer records.
encryption | Encoding data to prevent unauthorized access | All sensitive files must use encryption before being sent externally.
VPN | Virtual Private Network ‚Äî secure, encrypted connection over a public network | Employees must use the VPN when working from home.
two-factor authentication | Verification requiring two different methods of identification | Enable two-factor authentication to add an extra layer of security.
firewall | Network security system that monitors and controls incoming and outgoing traffic | The firewall blocked suspicious traffic from reaching our servers.
penetration testing | Authorized simulated cyberattack to evaluate system security | We hired experts to conduct penetration testing on our network.
patch | Software update that fixes security vulnerabilities | You should install the security patch as soon as it becomes available.
compliance | Following rules, regulations, and standards | Our company must maintain compliance with data protection laws.
risk assessment | Identifying and evaluating potential security threats | The annual risk assessment revealed several vulnerabilities.
incident response | Procedures for handling security breaches | The incident response team contained the breach within two hours.
access control | Restricting system access to authorized users only | Strict access control ensures only managers can view salary information.
zero-day exploit | Attack on an unknown vulnerability before a patch is available | Zero-day exploits are dangerous because there's no defense ready.
intrusion detection system | System that monitors network activity for malicious behavior | The intrusion detection system alerted us to unusual login attempts.
credential | Login information including username and password | Never share your credentials with anyone, including IT staff.
authenticate | To verify the identity of a user or system | Users must authenticate using their employee ID and password.
```

