**Exercise 2: Match the Threat to the Protection**

Draw a line connecting each cyber threat to the security measure that best prevents it.

| Threat | Protection |
|--------|------------|
| 1. Phishing attacks | a. Regular software patches |
| 2. Unauthorized network access | b. Employee security training |
| 3. Password theft | c. Firewall |
| 4. Software vulnerabilities | d. Two-factor authentication |
| 5. Data interception during transmission | e. Encryption / VPN |

