## E. WRITING TASK (Homework)

### Assignment: Security Policy Draft

**Sub-CPMK:** LO6.2 (Professional Security Policy Writing)

#### Task Description

Write a security policy draft (200-250 words) for an organization. Choose ONE of the following policy areas:

- **Option A:** Password Security Policy
- **Option B:** Email Security Policy
- **Option C:** Remote Work Security Policy

#### Requirements Checklist

Your policy MUST include:

| Requirement | Check |
|-------------|-------|
| Policy title and purpose statement | ‚òê |
| At least 4 specific rules using modal verbs | ‚òê |
| At least 2 obligations (must/have to) | ‚òê |
| At least 2 recommendations (should/ought to) | ‚òê |
| At least 2 prohibitions (must not) | ‚òê |
| Consequences for non-compliance | ‚òê |
| Minimum 5 cybersecurity vocabulary terms | ‚òê |
| 200-250 words | ‚òê |

#### Policy Structure Guide

**Section 1: Title & Purpose (2-3 sentences)**
- Policy name
- What the policy covers
- Why it's important

**Section 2: Requirements (4-6 sentences)**
- What employees must do (obligations)
- What employees should do (recommendations)

**Section 3: Prohibitions (2-3 sentences)**
- What employees must not do

**Section 4: Consequences (1-2 sentences)**
- What happens if employees violate the policy

#### Model Answer

> **Email Security Policy**
>
> **Purpose:** This policy establishes guidelines for secure email communication to protect company data and prevent cyber attacks.
>
> **Requirements:**
> All employees must verify the sender's email address before clicking any links or downloading attachments. Staff should be especially cautious with emails requesting urgent action or sensitive information. Employees have to report suspicious emails to the IT security team at security@company.com within 24 hours. Users ought to regularly review their spam folder settings and keep their email client updated.
>
> **Prohibitions:**
> Employees must not open attachments from unknown or untrusted sources. Staff must not forward company emails to personal email accounts. Users must not respond to emails requesting passwords or financial information ‚Äî legitimate organizations will never ask for this via email.
>
> **Consequences:**
> Violations of this policy may result in disciplinary action, including written warnings, suspension of email privileges, or termination depending on the severity of the breach.
>
> Remember: Phishing attacks are one of the biggest threats to our organization. When in doubt, verify before you click.

*Word count: 185 words*

**Note:** The model answer is slightly shorter than required. Your policy should be 200-250 words with more specific details.

---

### Assessment Rubric

Your writing will be assessed using this rubric:

| Criterion | Excellent (5) | Good (4) | Fair (3) | Needs Work (2) | Poor (1) |
|-----------|---------------|----------|----------|----------------|----------|
| **Content & Structure** | All required sections with excellent detail | Most sections with good detail | Most sections but limited detail | Several sections missing | Many sections missing |
| **Modal Verb Usage** | 6+ modals used correctly (must, should, must not) | 5 modals used correctly | 4 modals with minor errors | 2-3 modals with errors | 0-1 correct modals |
| **Cybersecurity Vocabulary** | 7+ relevant terms used correctly | 5-6 terms used correctly | 4 terms used correctly | 2-3 terms used | 0-1 terms used |
| **Professional Tone** | Consistently formal and professional | Mostly formal | Sometimes informal | Often informal | Inappropriate tone |
| **Organization** | Clear structure, logical flow | Good structure | Some structure | Poor structure | No clear structure |

**Total: _____ / 25 points**

#### Submission Details

| Item | Details |
|------|---------|
| **Due Date** | Next class meeting |
| **Format** | Printed (preferred) or digital submission |
| **File Name** | `[YourName]_Meeting06_SecurityPolicy.docx` |
| **Font** | Times New Roman or Arial, 12pt |
