## Answer Key for Self-Study Exercises

### Vocabulary Exercise 1
1. ransomware
2. encryption
3. VPN
4. phishing
5. compliance
6. firewall

### Vocabulary Exercise 2
1-b, 2-c, 3-d, 4-a, 5-e

### Vocabulary Exercise 3
- authenticate ‚Üí authentication
- comply ‚Üí compliant
- secure ‚Üí security
- authorize ‚Üí authorized

### Grammar Exercise 1
1. must (mandatory = obligation)
2. must not (prohibition)
3. should (good idea = advice)
4. have to (legal requirement)
5. don't have to (not necessary)
6. must not (strictly forbidden)
7. ought to (highly recommended)
8. might (still waiting = uncertain)
9. will (certain consequence)
10. had better (strong warning)

### Grammar Exercise 2
1. must / has to
2. must not
3. should
4. will
5. ought to
6. don't have to
7. must not
8. might / may
9. had better
10. must / has to

### Grammar Exercise 3
1. All staff must ~~to~~ complete... ‚Üí "must complete"
2. You ~~don't must~~ must not share... ‚Üí "must not share"
3. Employees should ~~to~~ report... ‚Üí "should report"
4. The company ~~musts~~ must comply... ‚Üí "must comply"
5. Users must not ~~to~~ click... ‚Üí "must not click"
6. Organizations should ~~conducts~~ conduct... ‚Üí "should conduct"
7. Cyber attacks will ~~to~~ become... ‚Üí "will become"
8. Staff ~~have not to~~ don't have to use... ‚Üí "don't have to use"
9. You ~~hadn't~~ had better not ignore... ‚Üí "had better not"
10. IT teams ought ~~‚àÖ~~ to review... ‚Üí "ought to review"

